Global Fluidised Catalytic Cracking Catalyst Additive Market Insights
Fluidised Catalytic Cracking Catalyst Additive Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Fluidised Catalytic Cracking Catalyst Additive Market Overview
The Fluidised Catalytic Cracking (FCC) Catalyst Additive market has witnessed significant growth, driven by increasing demand for petroleum refining and the growing need for cleaner fuels. The market is expected to reach a market value of approximately USD 3.2 billion by 2027, reflecting a steady compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 4.5%. The catalyst additives are critical in enhancing the performance of FCC processes, increasing the yield of valuable products like gasoline, diesel, and propylene while minimizing harmful emissions. With growing environmental regulations and the emphasis on refining processes, the market continues to expand globally.

